handist.collections.dist

Class DistCol<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • handist.collections.dist.AbstractDistCollection
      • handist.collections.dist.DistCol<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements handled by this DistCol
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class DistCol<T>
extends AbstractDistCollection
    A class for handling objects at multiple places. It is allowed to add new elements dynamically. This class provides the method for load balancing.

    Note: In the current implementation, there are some limitations.

    • There is only one load balancing method: the method flattens the number of elements of the all places.

        public DistCol()
        Create a new DistCol. All the hosts participating in the distributed computation are susceptible to handle the created instance. This constructor is equivalent to calling DistCol(TeamedPlaceGroup) with TeamedPlaceGroup.getWorld() as argument.
